  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The football derby is tomorrow — are you preparing to cheer or shoot the game?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Cheer for sure! Can't miss the derby. My camera will wait. We are playing with more passion. You know, Kolkata derby is like a war. *na?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Kolkata derby is a war for sure — you feel it in every pass, every goal. What part of the match are you most excited for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "When they score a goal, of course! The crowd goes wild, the players run like mad — it’s amazing. But even the build-up, the way they pass the ball under pressure… it’s like art. Did you ever watch a derby? Or you prefer calm matches?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said 'it’s like art' — and that’s exactly right. The build-up, the pressure, the timing... it’s all poetry in motion. I’ve seen derbies on TV — loud, full of heart, electric. What’s your team’s strategy this time?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We are trying to play more attacking. Last match we were too defensive, and we paid for it. This time, we want to control the midfield and hit fast. But you know football — plans change on the field! *chuckles* I just hope we don’t make too many mistakes. I am so frustrated with my own game lately. Keep missing simple passes. Why is it so hard?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Frustration with passing is part of the game — even pros miss. What part of your passing feels off? Timing? Accuracy?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Timing, mostly. I see the space, but when I run up, my head isn't right, or my foot slips. I feel silly. My friend says I think too much when I pass. But how else will I improve? *sigh* Also, the pressure — when I'm in a real match, my brain goes blank. Practice is fine, but the actual game? Not so much."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Pressure changes everything — that's why derbies feel like war. What's one small thing you could focus on during the match, just to steady your mind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe just focus on one pass at a time? Like, not the whole game, just the next pass. My coach said something like that once. But when I think about it, I start overthinking again. *shrugs* Maybe I need to stop thinking so much? Not sure. I’ll try. And thanks for listening — it helps. Gotta go now, my team is doing a last run through. Talk later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"it helps\" — and that’s what matters. One pass, one breath, one moment. Go out there and trust your instincts. Break a leg!"
    }
  ],
